
Verizon Perl Tools

Verizon Perl Tools is a collection of Perl modules which provides a
simple and consistent application programming interface to Verizon's
Cloud Offerings: 

	Enterprise Cloud
	Verizon Cloud Compute
	Verizon Cloud Storage

There is also a command line internface for these tools that illustrates their usage
and provides a convenient utility for system administrators and developers.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

or use CPAN:

       cpan> install Verizon::Perl::Tools

USAGE

  
SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Verizon::Perl::Tools

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Verizon-Perl-Tools

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Verizon-Perl-Tools

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Verizon-Perl-Tools

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Verizon-Perl-Tools/


